Class BlockSelectionWhenHigher

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.model.DivinityDecoratorWithEffects
it.polimi.ingsw.model.cards.BlockSelectionWhenHigher
All Implemented Interfaces:
Divinity
public class BlockSelectionWhenHigher
extends DivinityDecoratorWithEffects
Additional layer other divinities are wrapped into if Hypnus is in game.

At the start of a player's turn, if one of the worker is on a higher level than the others, the first cannot be selected

    • move

      public java.util.List<ModelUpdate> move​(Board board, Worker selectedWorker, Tile selectedTile)
      The move is overwritten so that once a player's has moved, the blocking condition is removed.

      This "trick" works because a worker is affected by the condition only on the first move so that it cannot be selected; for divinities that can move more than once, the effects is thus removed after moving a first time.

      Specified by:
      move in interface Divinity
      Overrides:

      Parameters:
      board - current Board
      selectedWorker - Selected worker from the Match
      selectedTile - Tile to move onto
      Returns:
      list of tiles to be modified on the view
